          @rmadrid28: I did look up the stats since the beginning of the 09/10 season (for CL and La Liga) and from that I have to conclude that in La Liga games Ronaldo does actually shoot quite some more penalties even despite playing fewer games: La Liga: Ronaldo has a total of 207 goals in 187 games (1.11 per game) of which 44/47 penalties (93.6%). (163/187 = 0.87 non-penalty goals per game) Messi has a total of 216 goals in 193 games (1.12 per game) of which 27/30 penalties (90.0%). (189/193 = 0.98 non-penalty goals per game) CL: Ronaldo has a total of 59 goals in 57 games (1.04 per game) of which 6/8 penalties (75.0%). (53/57 = 0.93 non-penalty goals per game) Messi has a total of 61 goals in 60 games (1.02 per game) of which 7/10 penalties (70.0%). (54/60 = 0.9 non-penalty goals per game) Other than that one actually has to acknowledge that these are some incredible goal ratios for both of them.
